I have a lot of respect for Bungie for continuing to put care into this experimental game mode, and constantly listening to player feedback. Love The Drifter, and love the game mode.

Gambit is the reason my gf got into the game because it's one of the most accessible aspects of Destiny 2. It's the perfect blend of PVE and PVP for those who are bored by one or gatekept by the other, and I don't even know of any games that have something similar.

Gambit fucks, and just because you're upset that you actually have to aim your weapons now is not a game mode's problem. Bungie constantly talks about moving the game in the direction of gun-focused play; that doesn't mean guns should wipe out teams in one shot even if they miss.

Thought Gambit was trending because of the character, but I guess it's because of a weak-ass take on the sport in Destiny 2? If the flagship of that argument is that rocket launchers track Guardians less intensely, then might I point you to PVP's effect on Stasis. #Destiny2
